goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield data, giving a good idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield of different varieties of barley compare?
goals.visualization: Grouped bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A grouped bar chart will allow for easy comparison of the yield of different varieties of barley, highlighting any significant differences.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield vs nitrogen level
goals.rationale: A scatter plot will show the relationship between yield and nitrogen level, allowing for the identification of any trends or patterns.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield across all sites?
goals.rationale: A histogram will show the frequency distribution of yield across all sites, giving an idea of the shape of the distribution and any outliers.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of yield by year
goals.rationale: A line chart will show the trend in yield over time, highlighting any changes or patterns in the data.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['yield'])
    plt.title("What is the average yield of barley across all sites?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Sites")
    plt.ylabel("Yield")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    grouped_data = data.groupby(['variety', 'year'])['yield'].mean().unstack()
    grouped_data.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title("How does the yield of different varieties of barley compare?")
    plt.xlabel("Variety")
    plt.ylabel("Yield")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.legend(title="Year")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('Year')['Yield'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped.index, data_grouped.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
